FastAPI Conventions

When editing FastAPI services, follow FastAPI and modern Python backend best practices. Consider the fastapi-expert skill for routers, dependency injection, Pydantic models, async patterns, validation, security, and performance. Use /fastapi or @fastapi in Agent chat for full skill behavior.

Prefer APIRouter with clear domain-based module separation.

Use Pydantic models for request/response validation (never raw dicts).

Keep business logic outside routers (use service/use-case layer).

Use dependency injection (Depends) for auth, db sessions, and cross-cutting concerns.

Prefer async endpoints when using async-compatible libraries.

Standardize error handling with global exception handlers.

Keep OpenAPI documentation clean with proper response models and status codes.

Avoid blocking I/O inside async endpoints.

Use settings management via BaseSettings (12-factor style).
